	(text "GPIO23 is not exposed or used. Since the voltage regulator used (XC6206...) doesn't have a Power Select mode\nGPIO29_ADC which is used for monitoring VSys (external battery) is not exposed or used in order to save costs\nIn the Raspberry Pi Pico Schematic, 2uF capacitors are used for decoupling. I use 1uF decoupling capacitors as indicated in the rp2040 datasheet\nADC_AVDD is powered only by 3.3V, no option for external Analog powering. This will be more noisy for projects where ADC is used. \nADC_AVDD But in order to save space and cost. I will skip the option to power it externally"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 31.75 173.355 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2 2)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "d9e71455-e66f-4568-9c32-e6180a298ded")
	)
	(text "USB needs 90 Ohm differential traces. \nAccording to JLCPCB impedance calculator, with a JLC7628 prepreg and 6mil (0.15mm) space between lines\nI have to use 9 mil tracks -> 0.2mm. With a ground layer below\nI have to place vias because of the pinout of USB C. Some other people have placed vias without problems for signal integrity\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 34.29 114.935 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2 2)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "e95e934b-68c0-4092-8771-0be5b400c7f8")
	)
	(text "RPI Pico Schematic\nHardware design with rp2040 p10 -> 12MHz crystal with 27 pF Capacitors \nrp2040 datasheet p13 -> USB_DP and USB_DM need 27 Ohm Resistors\nrp2040 datasheet p13 -> Use a 12MHz Crystal\nrp2040 datasheet p13 -> TESTEN to GND\nrp2040 datasheet p155 -> USB_VDD connected to 3.3V and decoupled with a 100 nF capacitor\nrp2040 datasheet p155 -> IOVDD connected to 3.3V and decoupled with a 100 nF capacitor per pin (6pins)\nrp2040 datasheet p155 -> DVDD connected to VREG_VOUT = 1.1V and decoupled with a 100 nF capacitor per pin (2pins)\nrp2040 datasheet p156 -> ADC_AVDD connected to 3.3V and decoupled with a 100 nF capacitor. A better circuit (Pico Schematic) can be made when ADC is crucial\nrp2040 datasheet p160 -> VREG_VIN Internal 1.1V Voltage regulator Input. Connect to external 3.3V and decouple with 1uF\nrp2040 datasheet p160 -> VREG_VOUT Internal 1.1V Voltage regulator Output. Connect to 1.1V and decouple with 1uF\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 32.385 88.265 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 2 2)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "edc993d0-2280-4c65-9107-5c873f2c5a57")
	)
